AGI - The People's Party (Pp), to the opposition in Spain, removed a video against the government, generated by artificial intelligence and nicknamed 'Corruption Island', which portrayed Prime Minister Pedro Sanchez in bare torso, following the complaints of the Dominican Republic, where the clip was set. The video also shows the wife of the premier, Begona Gomez, former Minister of Transport Jose Luis Abalos and other figures related to the Socialist Party of Sanchez with accusations of corruption.
Everyone appears in a swimsuit on an idyllic beach in the video that the Pp has now removed from its X account. The clip imitates the opening theme of the Spanish edition of the popular reality show 'Temptation Island', shot in Dominican Republic. It presents a map of the Caribbean nation and its flag along with the words "lussuria", "ambizione" and "bugie".
<div </div
&nbsp;
The Pp apologized and removed the video last night after the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Dominican Republic "shortly rejected" what defined a "malvolous and incomprehensible attack". "The exploitation of the image of the country and the distortion of its national symbols are unacceptable, and are even worse when they are for Spanish internal political reasons," he added. Sanchez apologized "with the Dominican Republic and its people for this shameful video". "The people who published it will have to respond," he warned.
Spanish Foreign Minister, Jose Manuel Albares, attacked the PP hard to "have openly embraced the communication strategies of the extreme right, with insults, slander and the use of artificial intelligence". He said that the People's Party caused a " diplomatic incident" with the "fraternal people" of the Dominican Republic, a former Spanish colony.&nbsp;
&nbsp;

